  "page": "A Feast for Crows-Chapter 27",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:rgb(213, 70, 30)\">Jaime III</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> chapter</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/A_feast_for_crows\" title=\"A feast for crows\"><img alt=\"AFeastForCrows.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/AFeastForCrows.jpg/220px-AFeastForCrows.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"354\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a3/AFeastForCrows.jpg/330px-AFeastForCrows.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/a/a3/AFeastForCrows.jpg/440px-AFeastForCrows.jpg 2x\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">POV</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Hayford\" title=\"Hayford\">Hayford</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Sow%27s_Horn\" title=\"Sow&#39;s Horn\">Sow's Horn</a> - <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Page</th><td>\n391 <small>UK HC</small> <small>(<a href=\"/index.php/Chapters_Table_of_contents\" title=\"Chapters Table of contents\">Other versions</a>)</small></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:rgb(213, 70, 30)\">Chapter chronology <small>(<a href=\"/index.php/Chapters\" title=\"Chapters\">All</a>)</small></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_16\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 16\">Jaime II</a><br />↑</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width:33%; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;\"><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_26\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 26\">Samwell III</a></td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\">&#160;←</td>\n<td style=\"width:33%; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; padding-right:0.1em; padding-left:0.1em;\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Jaime III</a></td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:middle;\">→&#160;</td>\n<td style=\"width:33%; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;\"><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_28\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 28\">Cersei VI</a></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n↓<br /><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_30\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 30\">Jaime IV</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Synopsis\">Synopsis</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_27&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Synopsis\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Aware that <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei</a> is trying to rid herself of him, <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime</a> argues that his place is beside the king, not off laying siege to <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>. But his sister responds that she can't rely on <a href=\"/index.php/Daven_Lannister\" title=\"Daven Lannister\">Daven</a>, and needs Jaime to defeat <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Tully\" title=\"Brynden Tully\">Brynden Tully</a>, as well as find out why <a href=\"/index.php/The_Mountain%27s_men\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Mountain&#39;s men\">Gregor's men</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> have not released <a href=\"/index.php/Wylis_Manderly\" title=\"Wylis Manderly\">Wylis Manderly</a> as the crown requested. She states that <a href=\"/index.php/Osmund_Kettleblack\" title=\"Osmund Kettleblack\">Osmund Kettleblack</a> will command the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> in his absence, although Jaime dislikes the idea.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4f/JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg/300px-JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"288\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4f/JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg/450px-JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/4f/JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg/600px-JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:JaimeLannisterTraining_by_Joshuacairos.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> training with Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>, by Joshua Cairós © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Jaime's command consists of <a href=\"/index.php/Kennos_of_Kayce\" title=\"Kennos of Kayce\">Kennos</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Dermot\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dermot\">Dermot</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lyle_Crakehall\" title=\"Lyle Crakehall\">Strongboar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Ronnet_Connington\" title=\"Ronnet Connington\">Red Ronnet</a>, as well as <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Marbrand\" title=\"Addam Marbrand\">Addam Marbrand</a>, whom Jaime demanded as concessions from his sister. \n</p><p>On the first night, they guest at Castle <a href=\"/index.php/Hayford\" title=\"Hayford\">Hayford</a>, and Jaime considers the fate of his cousin <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrek_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrek Lannister\">Tyrek</a>, who would be lord of the castle were he not missing. He thinks it possible the boy is still alive, perhaps having been secreted off by command of <a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a>, who very well could have known that the riot would occur.\n</p><p>Starting that night, Ser Jaime begins training every night with Ilyn Payne, in the hopes that he can become a proficient swordsman with his left hand. The company also visits <a href=\"/index.php/Sow%27s_Horn\" title=\"Sow&#39;s Horn\">Sow's Horn</a> and meets with Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Roger_Hogg\" title=\"Roger Hogg\">Roger Hogg</a>.\n</p><p>Arriving at <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a>, Jaime has Gregor Clegane's men release all prisoners, including Wylis Manderly, and then leaves Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Bonifer_Hasty\" title=\"Bonifer Hasty\">Bonifer Hasty</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Holy_Hundred\" title=\"Holy Hundred\">Holy Hundred</a> to hold the castle until <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> takes up its lordship. Jaime commands Bonifer to kill <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Thoros_of_Myr\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thoros of Myr\">Thoros of Myr</a> if either are captured, but requests he send him any <a href=\"/index.php/Bloody_Mummers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bloody Mummers\">Bloody Mummers</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Beric_Dondarrion\" title=\"Beric Dondarrion\">Beric Dondarrion</a> should they fall into his hands. \n</p><p>Outside, Jaime comes across <a href=\"/index.php/Ronnet_Connington\" title=\"Ronnet Connington\">Ronnet Connington</a>, who mentions how he once was betrothed to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a>. When Ronnet mocks Brienne, Jaime hits him in the face with his golden hand and insists he call her by name.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_27&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>The synopsis was copied from Aol member vbkorik27 previously at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20080228051425/members.aol.com/vbkorik27/summary/legend.html\">[1]</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_27&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: External links\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tor.com/blogs/2014/06/a-read-of-ice-and-fire-a-feast-for-crows-part-19\">A Read of Ice and Fire: A Feast for Crows, Part 19</a>. Analyses and summary of the chapter by Leigh Butler.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403153210\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.078 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.355 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 214/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 890/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 7274/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1051/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0